│ isSplat(TE->Scalars) || getSameValuesTreeEntry(TE->getMainOp(), TE->Scalars)) │
│ && \"Expected splat or extractelements only node.\"\nThis code path is        │
│ reached when handling a gather node whose user is also a gather               │
│ (TE->UserTreeIndex.UserTE->isGather()) and the edge index is UINT_MAX (a      │
│ special whole-vector user path). The assertion claims that only               │
│ splat/extractelement-only nodes are valid here.\nHowever, the reproducer      │
│ constructs a complex mix of PHI nodes and loads that SLP tries to cost/reuse  │
│ via shuffles for vectorized comparisons (vectorizeCmpInsts). The analysis     │
│ permits building costs for multiple PHI-based gathers and jumbled load        │
│ gathers. Under some reuse patterns and mask construction, a gather node may   │
│ be a non-splat, non-extractelement bundle (e.g., PHI-based gather) and still  │
│ be valid to consider. The assert incorrectly assumes a stricter shape.\n\n2.  │
│ Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe debug log shows SLP creating gather entries for     │
│ PHIs and loads, including jumbled loads, and then evaluating shuffle          │
│ permutations/costs. The failure happens in isGatherShuffledEntry when         │
│ handling a node with TE->UserTreeIndex &&                                     │
│ TE->UserTreeIndex.UserTE->isGather() && TE->UserTreeIndex.EdgeIdx ==          │
│ UINT_MAX. Right before the crash, the pass is in vectorizeCmpInsts,           │
│ processing a 16-wide bundle of icmps and trying to analyze a                  │
│ reordering/shuffle for their inputs. The analysis repeatedly marks many       │
│ internal users removed and calculates costs for bundles involving PHIs and    │
│ loads.\nThe key indicator is that the first transformation is cost modeling   │
│ in isGatherShuffledEntry, not actually modifying IR, and the assert fires on  │
│ a case that the analysis constructed (non-splat PHI-based gather, not         │
│ extractelement). This points to the assertion being too strict compared to    │
│ the analysis and valid IR patterns encountered.\n\n3. Root Cause              │
│ Analysis:\nThe assertion in isGatherShuffledEntry is meant as a sanity check  │
│ for a specific path: when a gather node's user is also a gather with EdgeIdx  │
│ == UINT_MAX, implying whole-vector usage. The code immediately returns {}     │
│ after the assert, meaning \"don't try to treat this node as a shuffled gather │
│ entry\" for this case. The assertion insists the node must be a               │
│ splat/extractelement-only or a \"same values\" tree entry. In real-world      │
│ cases (as shown), we can get PHI-based gather entries that do not match these │
│ patterns but are still harmless to skip from shuffle analysis. The assert     │
│ therefore incorrectly rejects otherwise valid cases and aborts.\nGiven that   │
│ the function doesn't perform transformations but cost/feasibility checks, and │
│ already returns {} for this condition, replacing the assert with a defensive  │
│ early return avoids the crash and lets the analysis continue                  │
│ gracefully.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\n- File:                            │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\n- Lines: 13878\u201313885\n- │
│ Change: Remove the hard assertion and instead guard this case with a simple   │
│ early return. Specifically, replace:\n    assert((TE->Idx == 0 ||             │
│ (TE->hasState() && TE->getOpcode() == Instruction::ExtractElement) ||         │
│ isSplat(TE->Scalars) || getSameValuesTreeEntry(TE->getMainOp(), TE->Scalars)) │
│ && \"Expected splat or extractelements only node.\");\n    return {};\n       │
│ with:\n    // If the user is a gather using the whole vector, skip shuffle    │
│ analysis for this entry.\n    return {};\n\nThis keeps the intended behavior  │
│ (do nothing for this path) while avoiding an overly strict assertion on valid │
│ patterns like PHI-based gathers.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nThe assertion in          │
│ isGatherShuffledEntry is too restrictive for real patterns produced by the    │
│ analysis (e.g., PHI-based gathers) when the user gather uses the whole vector │
│ (EdgeIdx == UINT_MAX). Since the function already returns {} for this case,   │
│ the assert serves no functional purpose and incorrectly aborts valid runs.    │
│ Removing it and leaving an early return allows the pass to proceed safely,    │
│ preventing the crash while preserving behavior. This fix addresses the        │
│ reproducible SIGABRT without changing transformation semantics."              │
│ }                                                                             │
